The fight never ends.

This is something Tony has always known. Or at least something Tony has known ever since he first became Iron Man.

The fight never ends but the fight has ended him, this time.

Thanos has ended it all but, how are they supposed to move on?

summary: Opinion on *just* how much of a feminist statement endgame made?
question: Opinion on *just* how much of a feminist statement endgame made?
answer:
Not a hell of a big one.  They used their heavy hitter as removable plot armor, they killed the only 2 other women who featured heavily in the plot and reduced almost everyone else to a girl power scene.

I appreciate steps forward and the promise for more varied and developed women, but endgame wasn’t that.

I would also maybe argue that that’s not what endgame was supposed to be.  We were saying goodbye to characters and closing off an era.  It’s good it was better than the first Avengers for that, but it’s silly to pretend it was a huge feminist fuck yeah when it came off the tail of Black Panther, Captain Marvel and to a lesser extent Ragnarok.
